1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,919
[Usman] <i>I can't lie to Marcus.</i>

2
00:00:03,002 --> 00:00:04,254
<i>Why don't we just tell him the truth?</i>

3
00:00:04,337 --> 00:00:05,588
<i>You share the same goal anyway.</i>

4
00:00:05,672 --> 00:00:07,757
[Jalil] <i>Usman, he is not</i>
<i>part of this mission.</i>

5
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:11,219
It's possible he didn't work
with the people who ruined our island,

6
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:13,513
but those people still manipulated him.

7
00:00:13,596 --> 00:00:17,684
[Jalil] <i>So I hope you understand</i>
<i>why I can't trust him.</i>

8
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,436
- [Jalil] Sir, take a look at this.
- [Datu Rahman] <i>Those accusations</i>

9
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:21,730
<i>against me are not true.</i>

10
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:26,860
<i>Those firearms are dropped</i>
<i>into the ocean near our island.</i>

11
00:00:26,943 --> 00:00:31,406
<i>We keep and hide them to prevent</i>
<i>those with impure intentions</i>

12
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:34,200
<i>to illegally distribute those weapons.</i>

13
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,618
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes,</i>

14
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:39,372
<i>you need to keenly observe</i>
<i>the people around you.</i>

15
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:44,127
<i>The people behind of all this</i>
<i>might just be inside NLEA.</i>

16
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:48,047
[Dionisio] <i>Azuelo has finally</i>
<i>put his trust in Reyes.</i>

17
00:00:48,131 --> 00:00:51,885
<i>They now believe that someone</i>
<i>sabotaged Damai Island.</i>

18
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,970
[Manuel] <i>Just let him be.</i>

19
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:57,390
[in English] I have something
in mind for that man.

20
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,184
[Ethan] <i>It's just</i>
<i>a vacant lot here, ma'am.</i>

21
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,477
[Buster] <i>Based on the data packets,</i>

22
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,520
<i>the signal came from a mobile hotspot</i>

23
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,522
- <i>that's immediately turned off.</i>
- [Lara] <i>How can I relax, huh?!</i>

24
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:06,691
[Lara, in English] <i>I feel like</i>
<i>I'm losing control of everything!</i>

25
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:08,276
[Dionisio] <i>No one can know about this.</i>

26
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:10,653
Neutralize the area.
There are no civilians there!

27
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,238
[Dionisio] <i>You'll be ambushed!</i>

28
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:14,324
[Dionisio] <i>The plan cannot fail.</i>

29
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:15,700
I need your help.

30
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:18,661
[Marcus] <i>Datu Rahman and Jalil</i>
<i>are certainly being hunted down.</i>

31
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:19,871
<i>They can't be harmed.</i>

32
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:22,624
<i>I have to correct the mistakes</i>
<i>that happened on the island.</i>

33
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:24,167
I have to protect them.

34
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:26,211
[Marcus] <i>Brother, they can't die.</i>

35
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:29,631
A lot of secrets will be buried
should they perish.

36
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:32,634
[tense music playing]

37
00:01:35,053 --> 00:01:37,013
[mysterious theme music playing]

38
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,862
What will happen to Sir Marcus?

39
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:55,448
Yeah. How can we help him?

40
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:57,450
I don't think there's anything
we could do.

41
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:59,452
Apart from helping him solve this issue.

42
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,414
- Sir.
- [in English] Sir. Good evening.

43
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:04,916
[in English] Good evening.

44
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,503
[unsettling music playing]

45
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:09,504
[Usman] Hey!

46
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:11,714
What are you doing?!

47
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:14,050
Why, sir? Does it look bad?

48
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:16,928
You know I'm skilled at drawing, right?

49
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:20,807
Oh, here. Take a look at my masterpieces!

50
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,892
Wonderful, aren't they? Right-- Huh?

51
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:25,645
- Stop fooling around!
- You know, if Sir Marcus

52
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:27,772
and Major Espina sees that
you're done for.

53
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:30,066
Especially when those two
despise each other so much.

54
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,068
- Give it back, sir.
- [phone chimes]

55
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:33,444
Stop your tomfoolery.

56
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:35,613
Sabdani, guys,

57
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:38,158
they said Sir Marcus
is calling for a meeting.

58
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:39,075
Let's go.

59
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:45,498
Since all of you are now part
of Task Force Alpha,

60
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,083
you should all know

61
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:51,129
that we are currently
in the midst of a huge war.

62
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:53,715
A war that not many people are aware of.

63
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:55,925
And a war where not everyone
makes it out alive.

64
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,635
In this fight,

65
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:00,430
we've already lost four members.

66
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:05,977
Task Force Alpha
is at the forefront of this war.

67
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,563
To be honest, I'm not sure

68
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:11,816
if all of us would still be here
in the upcoming days.

69
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:15,486
So, if any of you wants to back out,

70
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:19,282
now's your chance.
While it's not too late.

71
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:22,994
[stirring music playing]

72
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,465
[in English] SPO1 Usman Sabdani, sir.

73
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,259
[in English] Ready for deployment.

74
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:40,136
Never backing down, no matter what.

75
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,513
I'll fight alongside you in any war, sir.

76
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:46,851
So will I, sir.
I'll fight with you 'til the end.

77
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:49,520
[in English] Count me in, sir.

78
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:52,232
I'm raring to go, sir.

79
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,400
No one left behind.

80
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,111
Same for me, sir. We're not backing down.

81
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:01,449
Sir Marcus.

82
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:03,618
Count me in too. I'm more than down.

83
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:06,412
["Maninindigan", by Marko Rudio playing]

84
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:20,593
‪[song concludes]

85
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,345
[reporters clamoring]

86
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:25,390
- [reporter 1] Hello, Agent Reyes!
- [reporter 2] Agent, a moment, please!

87
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:26,891
[reporter 1] Sir!

88
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,268
[reporters clamoring]

89
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:30,478
- [clamoring continues]
- [camera shutters clicking]

90
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:32,272
[officer 1] Move! Move aside!

91
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:34,399
[officer 2] Leave! Leave!

92
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:36,442
- [crowd clamoring]
- [tense music playing]

93
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,736
- [officer] Hey!
- [crowd clamoring]

94
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:41,072
[reporter 2] Wait! Wait, sir!

95
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:42,448
[reporter 1] Agent Reyes,

96
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:45,576
what can you say
about Datu Rahman's statement?

97
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,412
Is it true that you'll side with him?

98
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:50,999
Does this mean that you admit
that you made a mistake

99
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:53,126
on the encounter that happened
on Damai Island?

100
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,338
While our investigation is still ongoing,

101
00:04:57,422 --> 00:05:02,093
we will not be entertaining
any baseless assumptions.

102
00:05:02,176 --> 00:05:03,303
Is that clear?

103
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:04,887
[reporters and police clamoring]

104
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:09,350
[clamoring continues]

105
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:11,311
You should stay away
from the media for now.

106
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,187
[reporter 3] Sir!

107
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:16,065
Sir, just one more question!

108
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:18,401
[reporter 4] Here he comes. General!

109
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:19,485
General Villanueva!

110
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:22,322
General, what is your reaction
on Datu Rahman's statement

111
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,325
that the syndicate's protector
on gun smuggling

112
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:26,826
is among the ranks of NLEA itself?

113
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:31,622
[sighs] All criminals would claim
that they're innocent.

114
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,168
Should a criminal's words
be taken seriously?

115
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:41,007
Who in their right mind
would believe a criminal?

116
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,635
[reporter 4] But General,
how will you address the allegations?

117
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:48,181
Isn't it better to investigate
on it instead of ignoring it?

118
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:50,016
[reporter 5] General,
just a follow-up question!

119
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:52,310
What if the allegations are true?!

120
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:55,521
Then, I'll get going, Doc.
I'll do my rounds now.

121
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,565
- Thank you.
- And to you as well.

122
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:00,151
Doc, you have a visitor.

123
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:02,695
‪[inhales]

124
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:06,908
[pensive music playing]

125
00:06:06,991 --> 00:06:08,409
How are you? What happened?

126
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:09,702
I'm sorry, Ma.

127
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:41,275
Son, I saw Datu Rahman's video.

128
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,528
He mentioned your name.

129
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:50,451
Ma… What Datu Rahman is saying is true.

130
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,246
When I visited Damai Island,

131
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:56,082
that's when I proved
that he had nothing to do

132
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:58,876
with all the allegations
they are dumping on him.

133
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,380
The man behind all of this…

134
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:05,758
holds a position in NLEA.

135
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,469
Oh my God, dear…

136
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:11,013
Be even more careful, alright?

137
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:13,558
[in English] Yes, Ma.

138
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:18,563
Ma…

139
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:20,773
I noticed that…

140
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:23,276
Why is Jamilah not here right now?

141
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:27,238
She took a sick leave. Why do you ask?

142
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,116
Nothing.

143
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:33,244
I think I just got used to how
she's always around

144
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:35,121
whenever I pay you a visit.

145
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:42,837
[suspenseful music playing]

146
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:47,884
It's almost time.

147
00:07:52,096 --> 00:07:54,056
<i>Breaking news!</i>

148
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:57,185
<i>After the release of Datu Rahman's</i>
<i>viral video statement,</i>

149
00:07:57,268 --> 00:08:00,271
<i>the Palace has finally released</i>
<i>an official statement.</i>

150
00:08:00,354 --> 00:08:04,192
<i>Here is the Presidential</i>
<i>Chief of Staff, Ahmad Mustapha.</i>

151
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:09,489
[Arabic] In the name of Allah, blessings
and peace be upon the Messenger of Allah.

152
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:13,159
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you,
Datu Rahman.

153
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:16,329
[suspenseful music continues]

154
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:32,261
The public, the entire country,
has seen and heard

155
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,679
all of your statements.

156
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:40,520
But it will all be useless
if you remain in hiding.

157
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:43,523
[Ahmad] <i>If what you're saying is true,</i>

158
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:45,525
<i>prove it.</i>

159
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,819
Why did it have to come to this?!

160
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:52,031
[Ahmad] <i>I'll give you a chance.</i>

161
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:55,201
<i>Surrender yourself to me.</i>

162
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:58,371
<i>I'll give you two days.</i>

163
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,957
<i>Forty-eight whole hours.</i>

164
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:04,085
They can't get Datu Rahman.

165
00:09:04,168 --> 00:09:07,088
- Well, yes. 'Cause if that happens…
- [in English] It's over for us!

166
00:09:07,171 --> 00:09:08,965
- [tense music playing]
- [sighs heavily]

167
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:12,426
Do you guys think Datu Rahman
will turn himself in?

168
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,554
Should he surrender himself,

169
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:17,223
it's good to do so to Ahmad Mustapha.

170
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:19,892
That's right.
Because he's a Muslim brother.

171
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:23,437
He'll never betray Datu Rahman.

172
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:24,438
That's true.

173
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:27,441
It hurts to hear this, but…

174
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:30,820
no one else could understand Muslims

175
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:33,781
other than Muslims themselves.

176
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:37,493
I'll wait for you, brother.

177
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:39,453
<i>Prove it.</i>

178
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:44,417
<i>That you can be trusted by the people.</i>

179
00:09:46,377 --> 00:09:48,337
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you once again.

180
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,386
I can't tell you all of my plans!

181
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:57,555
Just trust me!

182
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:00,057
We know what we're doing.

183
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:32,923
[heavy breathing]

184
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:33,841
‪[tense music playing]

185
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,643
[exhales sharply]

186
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:57,782
[sighs] What the hell
are you doing, Musthapa?

187
00:11:00,242 --> 00:11:02,203
What the hell are you doing?

188
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:06,082
[breathing heavily]

189
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:11,671
[sharp exhale]

190
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:13,589
‪[music intensifies]

191
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:26,102
<i>Guys, this is insane!</i>

192
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:28,562
<i>So, what does this mean?</i>
<i>Everything's fake?</i>

193
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:32,650
<i>Is Datu Rahman's video where he killed</i>
<i>two handsome police officers fake?</i>

194
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,361
[in English] <i>Are we being</i>
<i>catfished by the news?</i>

195
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:38,072
[in English] <i>This is crazy! My goodness!</i>

196
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:41,784
<i>Wow, time is the ultimate</i>
<i>truth teller, isn't it?</i>

197
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:43,994
<i>You're right.</i>
<i>The truth came out on its own.</i>

198
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:46,205
<i>Who could be doing this to Datu Rahman?</i>

199
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:47,832
<i>But, dude, the real question is…</i>

200
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:49,917
<i>Do you think Datu Rahman will surrender?</i>

201
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,837
<i>Will he be able to reach Mustapha alive?</i>

202
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,797
<i>Or will he be killed instantly?</i>

203
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,382
<i>What do you guys think?</i>

204
00:11:56,465 --> 00:11:59,552
<i>Luckily, Sir Mustapha acted quickly.</i>

205
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:03,431
At least we know there are people like him
in the government, right?

206
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:07,601
<i>But the sad thing is,</i>
<i>if Sir Mustapha wasn't a Muslim,</i>

207
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:12,064
<i>I'm sure, until now,</i>
<i>no one has helped Datu Rahman.</i>

208
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:14,316
So, Datu Rahman…

209
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:18,237
whatever your plan is…

210
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,239
<i>Be careful.</i>

211
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:23,242
<i>Don't be afraid!</i>

212
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:28,372
<i>Tell the truth for all of us!</i>

213
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:30,791
[In Arabic] <i>God is great!</i>

214
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,751
[tense music playing]

215
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,214
‪[inaudible]

216
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:56,192
- [woman] Edrick.
- [moans]

217
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,693
Edrick!

218
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,779
Come on!

219
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,364
You scared me!

220
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:06,368
You're clocked in,
but you're just sleeping around.

221
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:09,121
Get ready! We're going somewhere.

222
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:11,499
Where are we going?

223
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:14,710
To Zamboanga, on Damai Island. Let's go!

224
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,213
Hurry up! Hurry up!

225
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:19,590
‪[clicks tongue]

226
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:22,885
[in English] Wow!

227
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:27,890
Can you show me just once
that you love me?! Please!

228
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:35,523
[in English] We have to categorically
deny these claims.

229
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:38,234
Datu Rahman is saying nonsense!

230
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:39,527
[Dionisio, in English] I agree.

231
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,321
[Azuelo] General Villanueva.

232
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:46,534
How can we deny something

233
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:51,080
that we don't know is true or not?

234
00:13:52,289 --> 00:13:54,542
[in English] With all due respect, sir.

235
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,919
Our image is ruined in the public's eyes.

236
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:00,923
No one believes in us anymore.

237
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:02,383
[in English] That's preposterous.

238
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:06,428
And about what Datu Rahman is saying,

239
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:10,182
Agent Reyes and I have the same feeling.

240
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,435
The mission was sabotaged.

241
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:17,314
The footage of the operation was deleted.

242
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,776
And those syndicates

243
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,612
has protection on the inside.

244
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,698
You dare talk to us like this?

245
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:30,369
- This is insubordinate and unprofessional…
- If we want to improve our image,

246
00:14:30,452 --> 00:14:32,663
opticts can't be fixed!

247
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:38,127
We need to clean up the entire agency.

248
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:41,589
We should investigate it.

249
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,424
- [Paulino] Azuelo!
- [Dionisio] What is this man saying?!

250
00:14:43,507 --> 00:14:46,510
What do you want to say?
What do you want to do?

251
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:52,099
[Estrella] You won't stop
until the agency's image is ruined!

252
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:54,768
Are you betraying your peers?

253
00:14:55,769 --> 00:14:57,897
[in English] General Villanueva, may I?

254
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,648
[sighs, in English] Yes, Susan.

255
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:03,402
I think we need to show people
that we're fair.

256
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:05,738
That we're not taking sides.

257
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:08,699
And that we can hold accountable
those who are guilty,

258
00:15:08,782 --> 00:15:10,284
whether they're our colleagues or not.

259
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:13,704
Okay, Susan.

260
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:17,333
You speak to the press.

261
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:19,877
[suspenseful music playing]

262
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:31,722
[in English] See what you've done?

263
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:36,518
Young lady, all of this is happening

264
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:39,146
because you lost Datu Rahman!

265
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:47,112
If only you had been
more competent from the start,

266
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:50,699
I wouldn't have to worry
about something like this!

267
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:54,286
I trusted you, Lara!

268
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:55,663
And what have you done?!

269
00:15:56,372 --> 00:16:01,460
[in English] Now,
I have to fast-track everything!

270
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:03,879
Because I don't know

271
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:08,217
what Datu Rahman might reveal

272
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,678
if Mustapha gets to him first!

273
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:17,017
And if they manage to get
that old man and if he speaks

274
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,771
to the president's Chief of Staff…

275
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,357
we're done!

276
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:27,695
[morose music playing]

277
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:34,326
[sobs]

278
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:40,040
[sniffles]

279
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,183
[tense music stings]

280
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,278
[groans]

281
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:12,448
[tense music playing]

282
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:22,875
[Felix] Oh, hey. It's just you.

283
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,671
What happened to you?

284
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:33,177
I fought a guy in Damai Island once.

285
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,098
He did this.

286
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:41,310
That's crazy.

287
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,064
Do you know who he is?

288
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:46,690
[in English] Yes, sir.

289
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:52,404
This is him.

290
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,159
[tense music stings]

291
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:59,328
Jalil Abubakar.

292
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:05,667
I got lucky.

293
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,589
Are you sure you got lucky?

294
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,217
That scar is quite big.

295
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:18,639
It's a good thing… that he let you live.

296
00:18:19,848 --> 00:18:21,850
That, sir, is his mistake.

297
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,686
And when we met again…

298
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:29,024
I won't give him another chance.

299
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:29,942
‪[dramatic sting]

300
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:34,822
I'll kill that bastard.

301
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,617
Are you looking for him?

302
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,035
[in English] Actually, sir…

303
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:45,707
I'm hunting him.

304
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,421
Him and his criminal father.

305
00:19:01,348 --> 00:19:02,599
What happened there, sir?

306
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:12,818
Well…

307
00:19:12,901 --> 00:19:16,405
I had an encounter… with a bastard too.

308
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,160
But I'll get him back, eventually.

309
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,413
Ah.

310
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:28,667
I hope you get your revenge, sir.

311
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,004
I hope so, too.

312
00:19:37,301 --> 00:19:40,512
[Susan] The National
Law Enforcement Agency denies

313
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:43,974
all the allegations that the one
who caused this tragedy

314
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:46,310
is working in NLEA.

315
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:49,146
But in the spirit of fairness and justice,

316
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:52,566
the agency will continue
their investigation,

317
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:55,819
and if they are truly guilty,
we will not cover it up.

318
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:58,322
- [camera clicks]
- [suspenseful music playing]

319
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,362
<=ons> <?lang=> PRIMARY WITNESS

320
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:40,530
DATU RAHMAN ABUBAKAR ARRESTED
<=ons> <?lang=> FOR ILLEGAL ARMS SMUGGLING

321
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:55,921
[Marcus] <i>You are willing to do anything</i>
<i>to rescue your father.</i>

322
00:20:57,047 --> 00:21:00,384
<i>Even to the point</i>
<i>of risking your own life.</i>

323
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:06,306
<i>But the people behind this conspiracy</i>
<i>will not let you both live.</i>

324
00:21:07,015 --> 00:21:12,437
<i>So you have to work</i>
<i>with me, Jalil Abubakar,</i>

325
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,274
<i>before it is too late.</i>

326
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:22,406
[music fading]

327
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:24,992
[In Arabic] God is great.

328
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:30,414
[In Arabic] God is great.

329
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:35,794
[in Arabic] May the peace and mercy
of Allah be with you.

330
00:21:37,045 --> 00:21:39,256
[in Arabic] May the peace and mercy
of Allah be with you.

331
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:43,010
[unsettling music playing]

332
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,140
[In Arabic] God is great.

333
00:21:51,018 --> 00:21:52,602
[In Arabic] God is great.

334
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,188
[foreboding music playing]

335
00:22:07,951 --> 00:22:10,203
[in Arabic] May the peace and mercy
of Allah be with you.

336
00:22:12,205 --> 00:22:14,249
[in Arabic] May the peace and mercy
of Allah be with you.

337
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:17,169
‪[music intensifies, concludes]

338
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:24,468
[man] Just give her
the cheese bread, that's fine.

339
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:27,471
Give her the cheese bread.
How much are you taking?

340
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:29,931
- [woman 1] Six of them. Six!
- [man] You better pay for that!

341
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,683
- [woman 2, indistinct]
- [woman 1] I'll pay you later.

342
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:34,436
- [woman 2] A different one, please.
- [man, indistinct]

343
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:36,480
[woman] I don't like bitter melon.

344
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:40,692
- [man 1] Just grab some already.
- [man 2] I'll take some turon.

345
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:42,527
[woman 1] Why is there a cop here?

346
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,946
[woman 2] Oh no, he's probably here
to cause trouble again!

347
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,114
[man] Sir!

348
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:48,325
- [man] Sir, just a moment!
- [woman] Excuse me, sir!

349
00:22:48,408 --> 00:22:49,743
[woman] Why are you here?

350
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:54,414
[tense music playing]

351
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:01,171
What do you need here?

352
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:03,423
You're probably here
to cause trouble again, right?

353
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:06,593
We're not doing anything wrong.

354
00:23:07,302 --> 00:23:09,387
Yeah! Get out of here!

355
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:12,140
[Rashid] If you're here to arrest someone,

356
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:14,434
you're wasting your time.

357
00:23:15,018 --> 00:23:17,229
There are no criminals in our barangay.

358
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:21,817
I can assure you,
nothing will happen here.

359
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:26,154
I'm here to pick up Datu Rahman.

360
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:28,907
[tense music continues]

361
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:34,579
‪[dramatic stinging]

362
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:36,248
‪[dramatic sting]

363
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:43,797
Why did Datu Rahman
talk to you in his video?

364
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,841
Lara, what do you really want to know?

365
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:47,134
Did you talk to Datu Rahman?

366
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:48,385
Are you hiding something?

367
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,388
[woman] <i>Datu Rahman is not a criminal!</i>

368
00:23:51,471 --> 00:23:52,347
[Jalil] <i>I'm here to pick him up.</i>

369
00:23:52,430 --> 00:23:55,225
Jalil won't let anything happen to him.

370
00:23:55,308 --> 00:23:57,561
[man 1] <i>Next week,</i>
<i>the Japanese delegation will arrive.</i>

371
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:59,896
[man 2] <i>We want to hire you as consultant.</i>

372
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:02,023
[Azuelo] <i>Gather Task Force Alpha.</i>

373
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:04,067
<i>We have a VIP coming in</i>

374
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:06,778
<i>who needs maximum security protection.</i>

375
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:09,114
[Marcus] <i>Whoever this person is,</i>
<i>their life is in danger.</i>

376
00:24:09,197 --> 00:24:10,699
<i>And we need to protect them.</i>

377
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:12,576
There's a VIP coming here.

378
00:24:12,659 --> 00:24:16,037
You don't know anything!
You are not doing your job properly.

379
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,747
Looks like this guy is important.

380
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:26,214
The Muslims trust me.

381
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:28,884
<i>So I hope you in Task Force Alpha</i>

382
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,552
<i>do your job as well.</i>

383
00:24:30,635 --> 00:24:31,720
[screaming]

384
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:33,054
Don't touch me!

385
00:24:33,138 --> 00:24:35,348
Do you want me to kill that guy?

386
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:38,310
You're hiding something, Espina.
I'm going to find out what it is.
